🇺🇸🤝🇧🇷🏳️‍🌈 — Lula will be a bridge between the old and the new left in Latin America, says former US ambassador

The victory of Luiz Inácio Lula da Silva was received with relief and expectation in Washington, where speculation about a possible return of Trumpism to power is of great concern. In the view of Thomas Shannon, former ambassador to Brazil during PT governments and former undersecretary for Western Hemisphere Affairs at the State Department, the Biden administration, like many others, wants "Brazil back and more engaged with the international community".

Shannon believes that the relationship between Biden and Lula will be different to the one the president-elect had with former President Barack Obama, "because of the circumstances". "I see a new left in Latin America, which is not anti-American. Lula will be a bridge between the old and the new left", he says. In this context, he points out that "it is time for Latin American leaders to take on the issue of Venezuela without the US".
